New Records: Andrew Heaney earned his first win since July 21 against the Baltimore Orioles.
Key Match Events: The Texas Rangers secured a series-clinching win over the Los Angeles Angels.
Marcus Semien and Nathaniel Lowe provided early runs with a solo home run and a two-run home run, respectively.
Andrew Heaney allowed three earned runs on three hits and eight strikeouts in six innings.
Post-Match Reflections: Andrew Heaney expressed happiness about the win and praised his teammates' support.
Marcus Semien noted Heaney's strong performance despite a challenging season.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was significant as a series-clinching win for the Texas Rangers.
